# Backend Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the backend directory and add:

```
# Google Gemini API Configuration
# Get your key from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY="API_KEY"
```

## Usage

The backend will automatically load environment variables from `.env` file.

If `GEMINI_API_KEY` is not set:
- The server will still work and make predictions
- Health recommendations will show an error message
- A warning will appear in the logs

## Steps to Get Gemini API Key

1. Visit https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
2. Click "Create API key"
3. Copy the generated key
4. Paste it in this `.env` file
5. Restart the backend server

## Security

- Never commit `.env` file to version control
- `.env` is listed in `.gitignore` (if using git)
- Use secure environment variable management in production
- Rotate API keys regularly
